Package: ffmpeg2theora
Version: 0.29
Revision: 1
Description: Simple converter to create Ogg Theora files
License: GPL
Maintainer: Hanspeter Niederstrasser <nieder@users.sourceforge.net>
Depends: <<
	libavcodec54-0.11-shlibs,
	libavdevice54-0.11-shlibs,
	libavfilter2-0.11-shlibs,
	libavformat54-0.11-shlibs,
	libavutil51-0.11-shlibs,
	libiconv,
	libkate1-shlibs,
	libogg-shlibs,
	libpostproc52-0.11-shlibs,
	libswresample0-0.11-shlibs,
	libswscale2-0.11-shlibs,
	libtheoradec1-shlibs,
	libtheoraenc1-shlibs,
	libvorbis0-shlibs
<<
BuildDepends: <<
	libavcodec54-0.11-dev,
	libavdevice54-0.11-dev,
	libavfilter2-0.11-dev,
	libavformat54-0.11-dev,
	libavutil51-0.11-dev,
	libiconv-dev,
	libkate1-dev,
	libogg,
	libpostproc52-0.11-dev,
	libswresample0-0.11-dev,
	libswscale2-0.11-dev,
	libtheora0,
	libvorbis0,
	pkgconfig,
	scons
<<
Source: http://v2v.cc/~j/%n/downloads/%n-%v.tar.bz2
Source-MD5: 90855361d16d1d225fde094a5bae99f5
CompileScript: /usr/bin/true
InstallScript: <<
	#!/bin/sh -ev
	export PKG_CONFIG_PATH=%p/lib/ffmpeg-0.11/lib/pkgconfig
	%p/bin/scons install prefix=%p mandir=%p/share/man destdir=%d
	/bin/mkdir -p %i/share/man/man1
	/usr/bin/install -m 644 ffmpeg2theora.1 %i/share/man/man1
<<
DocFiles: AUTHORS COPYING ChangeLog INSTALL README TODO
Homepage: http://v2v.cc/~j/ffmpeg2theora/
DescDetail: <<
With ffmpeg2theora you can convert any file that ffmpeg can
decode to theora.
<<
DescUsage: <<
 ffmpeg2theora clip.avi
 
 will produce clip.ogv.  For more options run 'ffmpeg2theora -h'
<<
